com.topologi.diffx.sequence
Class PrefixMapping

java.lang.Object
  com.topologi.diffx.sequence.PrefixMapping

public final class PrefixMapping
extends java.lang.Object

Provides a mapping of namespace URIs to prefixes.

This class can be used to reconstruct the qualified element or attribute names.

Note that for each namespace URI there can only be one prefix.

add

public void add(java.lang.String uri,
                java.lang.String prefix)
         throws java.lang.NullPointerException
Add the specified mapping if the namespace URI has not beem mapped before.

This method will garantee that the mapping is actually unique, that is that the namespace URI correspond to one and only one prefix and that the prefix only corresponds to one and only one namespace URI.

Parameters:
uri - The namespace URI to map.
prefix - The prefix to use.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the URI or prefix is null
